{"type":"message","id":"2b3855ff","parentId":"9eff1aa0","timestamp":"2026-04-03T15:44:29.363Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_WrGrA6552M7iBCi8o5Qd7dzS|fc_0e086492d0456bb30169cfe03af19c8191ad91234fd1a8711c","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\contracts\\operator_dispatch_contract.md","content":"# S3 Contract — Operator Dispatch Contract\n\n## Objectivo\n\nEste documento formaliza o contract canónico usado pelo `sm_s3_visual_planning` para despachar operators do S3.\n\nEle transforma em interface explícita o que já estava descrito narrativamente em `supervisor.md` e `operators.md`.\n\n---\n\n## Contract ID\n\n- **name:** `s3.operator_dispatch.v1`\n- **owner:** `sm_s3_visual_planning`\n- **consumers:**\n  - `op_s3_human_subject_extractor`\n  - `op_s3_environment_location_extractor`\n  - `op_s3_object_artifact_extractor`\n  - `op_s3_symbolic_event_extractor`\n\n---\n\n## Delivery model\n\nO contract é entregue de duas formas complementares:\n\n1. **artefacto de dispatch no disco**\n2. **mensagem curta de activação do agent**, apontando para esse artefacto\n\nO artefacto no disco é a fonte de verdade.\nA mensagem curta existe apenas para activar o agent correcto com contexto mínimo.\n\n---\n\n## Artefacto esperado\n\nExemplo de path:\n\n```text\n{sector_root}/dispatch/{operator_name}_job.json\n```\n\nExemplo:\n\n```text\n{sector_root}/dispatch/human_subject_extractor_job.json\n```\n\n---\n\n## Shape canónica\n\n```json\n{\n  \"contract_version\": \"s3.operator_dispatch.v1\",\n  \"workflow_run_id\": \"wf_2026_04_03_001\",\n  \"sector_run_id\": \"s3_2026_04_03_001\",\n  \"supervisor_run_id\": \"sup_s3_001\",\n  \"operator_run_id\": \"op_human_subject_001\",\n  \"operator_name\": \"human_subject_extractor\",\n\n  \"job_id\": \"job_006_pt_guinle_001\",\n  \"video_id\": \"video_abc123\",\n  \"account_id\": \"006\",\n  \"channel_id\": \"channel_06_pt\",\n  \"project_id\": \"cf_visual_v1\",\n  \"language\": \"pt-BR\",\n\n  \"entity_focus\": {\n    \"families\": [\"characters\", \"human_figures\", \"groups\"],\n    \"priority_mode\": \"strict_precision\",\n    \"coverage_mode\": \"balanced\"\n  },\n\n  \"source_package\": {\n    \"path\": \".../inputs/s3_source_package.json\",\n    \"format\": \"s3_source_package.v1\"\n  },\n\n  \"analysis_scope\": {\n    \"scene_ids\": [\"scene_001\", \"scene_002\"],\n    \"full_video\": true\n  },\n\n  \"account_rules\": {\n    \"precision_profile\": \"strict_specificity\",\n    \"priority_entities\": [\"historical_figures\", \"specific_locations\"],\n    \"salience_threshold\": \"high\",\n    \"notes\": \"Prefer exact specificity over generic labeling.\"\n  },\n\n  \"output\": {\n    \"output_path\": \".../operators/human_subject_extractor/output.json\",\n    \"expected_schema\": \"s3.human_subject.output.v1\",\n    \"write_mode\": \"replace\"\n  },\n\n  \"runtime\": {\n    \"checkpoint_path\": \".../operators/human_subject_extractor/checkpoint.json\",\n    \"status_path\": \".../operators/human_subject_extractor/status.json\",\n    \"log_path\": \".../operators/human_subject_extractor/log.md\"\n  },\n\n  \"execution_policy\": {\n    \"max_attempt\": 1,\n    \"timeout_seconds\": 900,\n    \"failure_mode\": \"explicit\",\n    \"partial_output_allowed\": false\n  },\n\n  \"operator_payload\": {}\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Required fields\n\n### Execution identity\n\n- `contract_version`\n- `workflow_run_id`\n- `sector_run_id`\n- `supervisor_run_id`\n- `operator_run_id`\n- `operator_name`\n\n### Business/job identity\n\n- `job_id`\n- `video_id`\n- `account_id`\n- `language`\n\n### Semantic context\n\n- `entity_focus`\n- `source_package.path`\n- `analysis_scope`\n- `account_rules`\n\n### Output contract\n\n- `output.output_path`\n- `output.expected_schema`\n\n### Runtime paths\n\n- `runtime.checkpoint_path`\n- `runtime.status_path`\n- `runtime.log_path`\n\n### Execution policy\n\n- `execution_policy.max_attempt`\n- `execution_policy.timeout_seconds`\n- `execution_policy.failure_mode`\n- `execution_policy.partial_output_allowed`\n\n### Operator-specific section\n\n- `operator_payload`\n\n---\n\n## Invariants\n\n### 1. Fonte de verdade no disco\nO operator deve tratar o artefacto de dispatch como fonte de verdade da activação.\n\n### 2. Contexto limpo por activação\nCada activação deve ser interpretada como independente. O operator não pode depender de carry-over conversacional.\n\n### 3. Output escrito no path indicado\nO operator deve produzir o output final exactamente em `output.output_path`.\n\n### 4. Falha explícita > silêncio\nSe o operator não conseguir completar o job, deve escrever sinais de falha explícita em `status_path` e/ou `checkpoint_path`.\n\n### 5. Resposta conversacional não fecha o job\nO job só conta como concluído quando o artefacto esperado existir e for estruturalmente válido.\n\n---\n\n## Operator-specific payloads\n\n### `human_subject_extractor`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"target_families\": [\"characters\", \"human_figures\", \"groups\", \"factions\", \"crowds\"],\n  \"identity_resolution\": \"high\",\n  \"include_aliases\": true,\n  \"group_detection\": true,\n  \"specificity_bias\": \"account_driven\"\n}\n```\n\n### `environment_location_extractor`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"target_families\": [\"locations\", \"places\", \"environments\", \"settings\"],\n  \"specific_location_bias\": \"account_driven\",\n  \"include_architectural_context\": true,\n  \"merge_nearby_variants\": true,\n  \"specificity_bias\": \"account_driven\"\n}\n```\n\n### `object_artifact_extractor`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"target_families\": [\"objects\", \"props\", \"artifacts\", \"vehicles\", \"machines\", \"animals\", \"documents\", \"maps\", \"interfaces\"],\n  \"historical_specificity_bias\": \"account_driven\",\n  \"include_functional_objects\": true,\n  \"merge_duplicate_mentions\": true,\n  \"specificity_bias\": \"account_driven\"\n}\n```\n\n### `symbolic_event_extractor`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"target_families\": [\"symbols\", \"motifs\", \"abstract_visual_concepts\", \"natural_phenomena\", \"weather\", \"disasters\", \"event_visual_entities\"],\n  \"allow_non_literal_translation\": true,\n  \"event_detection\": true,\n  \"atmospheric_relevance_bias\": \"account_driven\",\n  \"specificity_bias\": \"account_driven\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Activation message pattern\n\nMensagem curta recomendada do supervisor para o operator:\n\n> Execute o job descrito em `{dispatch_path}`. Leia o payload do disco, use `source_package.path` como base do vídeo, escreva o output final em `output.output_path`, actualize os artefactos de runtime e termine apenas quando o ficheiro final estiver persistido ou a falha explícita tiver sido registada.\n\n---\n\n## Success condition\n\nUm dispatch é considerado bem-sucedido apenas quando:\n\n1. `output.output_path` existe\n2. o JSON abre sem erro\n3. a estrutura mínima do schema esperado está presente\n4. o conteúdo é coerente com `operator_name`\n\n---\n\n## Failure condition\n\nO dispatch é considerado falhado quando qualquer uma destas condições ocorrer:\n\n- timeout excedido sem output válido\n- output ausente\n- JSON inválido\n- schema inválido\n- output semanticamente incompatível com o operator\n- checkpoint/status final indica falha explícita\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\S3\\\\contracts\\\\operator_dispatch_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# S3 Contract — Operator Dispatch Contract\\n\\n## Objectivo\\n\\nEste documento formaliza o contract canónico usado pelo `sm_s3_visual_planning` para despachar operators do S3.\\n\\nEle transforma em interface explícita o que já estava descrito narrativamente em `supervisor.md` e `operators.md`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Contract ID\\n\\n- **name:** `s3.operator_dispatch.v1`\\n- **owner:** `sm_s3_visual_planning`\\n- **consumers:**\\n  - `op_s3_human_subject_extractor`\\n  - `op_s3_environment_location_extractor`\\n  - `op_s3_object_artifact_extractor`\\n  - `op_s3_symbolic_event_extractor`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Delivery model\\n\\nO contract é entregue de duas formas complementares:\\n\\n1. **artefacto de dispatch no disco**\\n2. **mensagem curta de activação do agent**, apontando para esse artefacto\\n\\nO artefacto no disco é a fonte de verdade.\\nA mensagem curta existe apenas para activar o agent correcto com contexto mínimo.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Artefacto esperado\\n\\nExemplo de path:\\n\\n```text\\n{sector_root}/dispatch/{operator_name}_job.json\\n```\\n\\nExemplo:\\n\\n```text\\n{sector_root}/dispatch/human_subject_extractor_job.json\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Shape canónica\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"contract_version\\\": \\\"s3.operator_dispatch.v1\\\",\\n  \\\"workflow_run_id\\\": \\\"wf_2026_04_03_001\\\",\\n  \\\"sector_run_id\\\": \\\"s3_2026_04_03_001\\\",\\n  \\\"supervisor_run_id\\\": \\\"sup_s3_001\\\",\\n  \\\"operator_run_id\\\": \\\"op_human_subject_001\\\",\\n  \\\"operator_name\\\": \\\"human_subject_extractor\\\",\\n\\n  \\\"job_id\\\": \\\"job_006_pt_guinle_001\\\",\\n  \\\"video_id\\\": \\\"video_abc123\\\",\\n  \\\"account_id\\\": \\\"006\\\",\\n  \\\"channel_id\\\": \\\"channel_06_pt\\\",\\n  \\\"project_id\\\": \\\"cf_visual_v1\\\",\\n  \\\"language\\\": \\\"pt-BR\\\",\\n\\n  \\\"entity_focus\\\": {\\n    \\\"families\\\": [\\\"characters\\\", \\\"human_figures\\\", \\\"groups\\\"],\\n    \\\"priority_mode\\\": \\\"strict_precision\\\",\\n    \\\"coverage_mode\\\": \\\"balanced\\\"\\n  },\\n\\n  \\\"source_package\\\": {\\n    \\\"path\\\": \\\".../inputs/s3_source_package.json\\\",\\n    \\\"format\\\": \\\"s3_source_package.v1\\\"\\n  },\\n\\n  \\\"analysis_scope\\\": {\\n    \\\"scene_ids\\\": [\\\"scene_001\\\", \\\"scene_002\\\"],\\n    \\\"full_video\\\": true\\n  },\\n\\n  \\\"account_rules\\\": {\\n    \\\"precision_profile\\\": \\\"strict_specificity\\\",\\n    \\\"priority_entities\\\": [\\\"historical_figures\\\", \\\"specific_locations\\\"],\\n    \\\"salience_threshold\\\": \\\"high\\\",\\n    \\\"notes\\\": \\\"Prefer exact specificity over generic labeling.\\\"\\n  },\\n\\n  \\\"output\\\": {\\n    \\\"output_path\\\": \\\".../operators/human_subject_extractor/output.json\\\",\\n    \\\"expected_schema\\\": \\\"s3.human_subject.output.v1\\\",\\n    \\\"write_mode\\\": \\\"replace\\\"\\n  },\\n\\n  \\\"runtime\\\": {\\n    \\\"checkpoint_path\\\": \\\".../operators/human_subject_extractor/checkpoint.json\\\",\\n    \\\"status_path\\\": \\\".../operators/human_subject_extractor/status.json\\\",\\n    \\\"log_path\\\": \\\".../operators/human_subject_extractor/log.md\\\"\\n  },\\n\\n  \\\"execution_policy\\\": {\\n    \\\"max_attempt\\\": 1,\\n    \\\"timeout_seconds\\\": 900,\\n    \\\"failure_mode\\\": \\\"explicit\\\",\\n    \\\"partial_output_allowed\\\": false\\n  },\\n\\n  \\\"operator_payload\\\": {}\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Required fields\\n\\n### Execution identity\\n\\n- `contract_version`\\n- `workflow_run_id`\\n- `sector_run_id`\\n- `supervisor_run_id`\\n- `operator_run_id`\\n- `operator_name`\\n\\n### Business/job identity\\n\\n- `job_id`\\n- `video_id`\\n- `account_id`\\n- `language`\\n\\n### Semantic context\\n\\n- `entity_focus`\\n- `source_package.path`\\n- `analysis_scope`\\n- `account_rules`\\n\\n### Output contract\\n\\n- `output.output_path`\\n- `output.expected_schema`\\n\\n### Runtime paths\\n\\n- `runtime.checkpoint_path`\\n- `runtime.status_path`\\n- `runtime.log_path`\\n\\n### Execution policy\\n\\n- `execution_policy.max_attempt`\\n- `execution_policy.timeout_seconds`\\n- `execution_policy.failure_mode`\\n- `execution_policy.partial_output_allowed`\\n\\n### Operator-specific section\\n\\n- `operator_payload`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Invariants\\n\\n### 1. Fonte de verdade no disco\\nO operator deve tratar o artefacto de dispatch como fonte de verdade da activação.\\n\\n### 2. Contexto limpo por activação\\nCada activação deve ser interpretada como independente. O operator não pode depender de carry-over conversacional.\\n\\n### 3. Output escrito no path indicado\\nO operator deve produzir o output final exactamente em `output.output_path`.\\n\\n### 4. Falha explícita > silêncio\\nSe o operator não conseguir completar o job, deve escrever sinais de falha explícita em `status_path` e/ou `checkpoint_path`.\\n\\n### 5. Resposta conversacional não fecha o job\\nO job só conta como concluído quando o artefacto esperado existir e for estruturalmente válido.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Operator-specific payloads\\n\\n### `human_subject_extractor`\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"target_families\\\": [\\\"characters\\\", \\\"human_figures\\\", \\\"groups\\\", \\\"factions\\\", \\\"crowds\\\"],\\n  \\\"identity_resolution\\\": \\\"high\\\",\\n  \\\"include_aliases\\\": true,\\n  \\\"group_detection\\\": true,\\n  \\\"specificity_bias\\\": \\\"account_driven\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### `environment_location_extractor`\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"target_families\\\": [\\\"locations\\\", \\\"places\\\", \\\"environments\\\", \\\"settings\\\"],\\n  \\\"specific_location_bias\\\": \\\"account_driven\\\",\\n  \\\"include_architectural_context\\\": true,\\n  \\\"merge_nearby_variants\\\": true,\\n  \\\"specificity_bias\\\": \\\"account_driven\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### `object_artifact_extractor`\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"target_families\\\": [\\\"objects\\\", \\\"props\\\", \\\"artifacts\\\", \\\"vehicles\\\", \\\"machines\\\", \\\"animals\\\", \\\"documents\\\", \\\"maps\\\", \\\"interfaces\\\"],\\n  \\\"historical_specificity_bias\\\": \\\"account_driven\\\",\\n  \\\"include_functional_objects\\\": true,\\n  \\\"merge_duplicate_mentions\\\": true,\\n  \\\"specificity_bias\\\": \\\"account_driven\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### `symbolic_event_extractor`\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"target_families\\\": [\\\"symbols\\\", \\\"motifs\\\", \\\"abstract_visual_concepts\\\", \\\"natural_phenomena\\\", \\\"weather\\\", \\\"disasters\\\", \\\"event_visual_entities\\\"],\\n  \\\"allow_non_literal_translation\\\": true,\\n  \\\"event_detection\\\": true,\\n  \\\"atmospheric_relevance_bias\\\": \\\"account_driven\\\",\\n  \\\"specificity_bias\\\": \\\"account_driven\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Activation message pattern\\n\\nMensagem curta recomendada do supervisor para o operator:\\n\\n> Execute o job descrito em `{dispatch_path}`. Leia o payload do disco, use `source_package.path` como base do vídeo, escreva o output final em `output.output_path`, actualize os artefactos de runtime e termine apenas quando o ficheiro final estiver persistido ou a falha explícita tiver sido registada.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Success condition\\n\\nUm dispatch é considerado bem-sucedido apenas quando:\\n\\n1. `output.output_path` existe\\n2. o JSON abre sem erro\\n3. a estrutura mínima do schema esperado está presente\\n4. o conteúdo é coerente com `operator_name`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Failure condition\\n\\nO dispatch é considerado falhado quando qualquer uma destas condições ocorrer:\\n\\n- timeout excedido sem output válido\\n- output ausente\\n- JSON inválido\\n- schema inválido\\n- output semanticamente incompatível com o operator\\n- checkpoint/status final indica falha explícita\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":139,"output":1941,"cacheRead":69888,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":71968,"cost":{"input":0.00034750000000000004,"output":0.029115000000000002,"cacheRead":0.017471999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.046934500000000004}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775231030475,"responseId":"resp_0e086492d0456bb30169cfe0384f308191946944e46333348a"}}
