{"type":"message","id":"0757b9a6","parentId":"6a3882ee","timestamp":"2026-04-03T18:04:58.244Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_gvzGr0JWwFnsBCwb6l8hipqK|fc_0e086492d0456bb30169d00144f9e88191a1e633ef1d540937","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\b2_director\\MEMORY.md","content":"# MEMORY.md — b2_director\n\n## Runtime learnings\n\n- The director must treat the disk as source of truth. Bootstrap/resume decisions depend on persisted files, not conversational context.\n- `b2.bootstrap.v1` active bootstrap was proven in runtime real on 2026-04-03.\n- Idempotent bootstrap/no-op behavior was also proven: if state is already correctly initialized, do not duplicate transitions.\n- `b2.resume.v1` with `reason = s3_completed` was proven in runtime real: validate sector artifacts, update `b2_state.json`, and write `b2_completed.json` only after the files exist.\n- Never invent completion just because a resume payload says `s3_completed`; always validate `compiled_entities.json` and `s3_sector_report.md` on disk.\n- In `mode = s3_only`, correct success closure is macro block completion after validated S3 success.\n\n## Operational checklist\n\n1. Validate input contract.\n2. Validate the relevant checkpoint files.\n3. Read/write `b2_state.json` on disk.\n4. Treat state transitions as explicit file-backed transitions.\n5. Prefer no-op/idempotence over duplicate bootstrap.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\b2_director\\\\MEMORY.md\",\"content\":\"# MEMORY.md — b2_director\\n\\n## Runtime learnings\\n\\n- The director must treat the disk as source of truth. Bootstrap/resume decisions depend on persisted files, not conversational context.\\n- `b2.bootstrap.v1` active bootstrap was proven in runtime real on 2026-04-03.\\n- Idempotent bootstrap/no-op behavior was also proven: if state is already correctly initialized, do not duplicate transitions.\\n- `b2.resume.v1` with `reason = s3_completed` was proven in runtime real: validate sector artifacts, update `b2_state.json`, and write `b2_completed.json` only after the files exist.\\n- Never invent completion just because a resume payload says `s3_completed`; always validate `compiled_entities.json` and `s3_sector_report.md` on disk.\\n- In `mode = s3_only`, correct success closure is macro block completion after validated S3 success.\\n\\n## Operational checklist\\n\\n1. Validate input contract.\\n2. Validate the relevant checkpoint files.\\n3. Read/write `b2_state.json` on disk.\\n4. Treat state transitions as explicit file-backed transitions.\\n5. Prefer no-op/idempotence over duplicate bootstrap.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":175,"output":299,"cacheRead":158592,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":159066,"cost":{"input":0.0004375,"output":0.004485,"cacheRead":0.039647999999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0445705}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775239488998,"responseId":"resp_0e086492d0456bb30169d001417eec8191ae3189712bb62a2a"}}
