{"type":"message","id":"e428b9da","parentId":"f00cdcd7","timestamp":"2026-04-03T18:05:13.901Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fQ1qOFviMPywFSm1CV0pzNLY|fc_0e086492d0456bb30169d0015743ac81919b7e90bcdf2e9d76","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s3_human_subject_extractor\\MEMORY.md","content":"# MEMORY.md — op_s3_human_subject_extractor\n\n## Runtime learnings\n\n- This operator was the first S3 operator to be proven with a real canonical output shape.\n- Success means both: the agent ran and the final `output.json` matched the canonical schema.\n- Do not rely on conversational summaries as proof; rely on `output.json`, `status.json`, and `checkpoint.json`.\n- Fresh activation should still succeed using only dispatch + source package + runtime file paths.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s3_human_subject_extractor\\\\MEMORY.md\",\"content\":\"# MEMORY.md — op_s3_human_subject_extractor\\n\\n## Runtime learnings\\n\\n- This operator was the first S3 operator to be proven with a real canonical output shape.\\n- Success means both: the agent ran and the final `output.json` matched the canonical schema.\\n- Do not rely on conversational summaries as proof; rely on `output.json`, `status.json`, and `checkpoint.json`.\\n- Fresh activation should still succeed using only dispatch + source package + runtime file paths.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":200,"output":151,"cacheRead":159232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":159583,"cost":{"input":0.0005,"output":0.002265,"cacheRead":0.039807999999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.042573}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775239507518,"responseId":"resp_0e086492d0456bb30169d00153f9448191872ee93f35f08029"}}
