{"type":"message","id":"a6a2fb77","parentId":"4936e6a1","timestamp":"2026-04-03T18:23:53.696Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou criar isso agora na estrutura certa: checklist oficial no B2, referência no postmortem e lembrança estratégica na memória principal.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e086492d0456bb30169d005a663448191bf1417e56931dda0\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_dngXYmFpdgrJFMAWJDybqgb6|fc_0e086492d0456bb30169d005a71a388191b747c11d8b30172f","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\SECTOR_PREFLIGHT_CHECKLIST.md","content":"# Sector Preflight Checklist\n\nUse this before opening any new Block 2 sector (S4, S5, S6, or future sub-sectors).\n\nThe goal is to prevent repeating the exact class of mistakes we hit during the first B2/S3 runtime validation cycle.\n\n---\n\n## A. Runtime materialization\n\n- [ ] Every required agent is **really** materialized in OpenClaw runtime\n- [ ] Every required agent appears in `openclaw agents list`\n- [ ] Every required agent can execute at least one real turn\n- [ ] No sector is considered \"real\" based only on folders/docs existing\n\n---\n\n## B. Contract freezing\n\n- [ ] Canonical input contract exists\n- [ ] Canonical output contract exists\n- [ ] Dispatch contract exists\n- [ ] Resume/reentry contract exists where applicable\n- [ ] Schema files exist for all outputs that matter\n- [ ] Version names are aligned (`v1` vs `v2`, etc.)\n\n---\n\n## C. Invocation primitive\n\n- [ ] The exact supervisor -> operator invocation primitive is frozen\n- [ ] The primitive is proven in this environment\n- [ ] No ambiguous fallback path remains as the default\n- [ ] If ACP is mentioned, its role is explicit and non-assumed\n\n### Current B2 default lesson\nFor the current environment, do **not** assume ACP as the default orchestration primitive.\nPrefer the proven path:\n\n```text\nexec -> openclaw agent --agent <agent_id> --message \"...\" --json\n```\n\n---\n\n## D. Dispatch integrity\n\n- [ ] Every operator dispatch file is generated\n- [ ] Every dispatch path matches the operator expectation\n- [ ] `operator_name` matches the actual target operator\n- [ ] `output.output_path` matches the intended runtime location\n- [ ] Schema id / expected schema matches the operator contract\n\n---\n\n## E. Operator validation\n\n- [ ] Each operator has been run at least once for real\n- [ ] Runtime success is proven by files, not by conversation alone\n- [ ] Each operator output was validated against the current canonical schema\n- [ ] Any legacy output shapes have been normalized or explicitly forbidden\n- [ ] `status.json` and `checkpoint.json` are written honestly\n\n---\n\n## F. Supervisor validation\n\n- [ ] Supervisor reads bootstrap from disk correctly\n- [ ] Supervisor writes activation plan correctly\n- [ ] Supervisor writes dispatches correctly\n- [ ] Supervisor validates operator artifacts on disk\n- [ ] Supervisor compile/report/checkpoints are based on real files\n- [ ] Disk artifacts match what the supervisor claims in chat\n\n---\n\n## G. Director / block control-plane validation\n\n- [ ] Block director active bootstrap is proven\n- [ ] Block director idempotent/no-op bootstrap is proven\n- [ ] Block director resume-success path is proven\n- [ ] Block director resume-failure path is proven (or explicitly deferred)\n- [ ] `state.json` mutations are verified on disk\n- [ ] Macro completion/failure checkpoints are verified on disk\n\n---\n\n## H. Truth model\n\n- [ ] Disk is treated as source of truth\n- [ ] Agent conversational summaries are treated as secondary evidence only\n- [ ] No completion is accepted without actual persisted artifacts\n- [ ] `degraded_completed` meaning is explicitly classified:\n  - [ ] degraded because runtime failed\n  - [ ] degraded because test scope intentionally ran a subset\n\n---\n\n## I. Production-mode realism\n\n- [ ] Tests are not relying on residual session memory as hidden glue\n- [ ] Activations are contract-complete and file-driven\n- [ ] The sector can tolerate fresh activation behavior\n- [ ] The sector does not depend on thread-bound session mythology\n\n---\n\n## J. Paperclip / Perseus readiness gate\n\nDo **not** let Paperclip rely on a new sector until all of the following are true:\n\n- [ ] Director path proven enough for the intended scope\n- [ ] Supervisor path proven enough for the intended scope\n- [ ] Required operators proven enough for the intended scope\n- [ ] Remaining degradation is test-scope only, not infra/runtime failure\n- [ ] Checkpoint/reentry loop is clear and operational\n\n---\n\n## Exit question\n\nBefore opening the next sector, answer this honestly:\n\n> If this sector fails tomorrow, will we know whether it failed because of runtime, dispatch, contract, state transition, or model behavior?\n\nIf the answer is **no**, the sector is not preflighted yet.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\SECTOR_PREFLIGHT_CHECKLIST.md\",\"content\":\"# Sector Preflight Checklist\\n\\nUse this before opening any new Block 2 sector (S4, S5, S6, or future sub-sectors).\\n\\nThe goal is to prevent repeating the exact class of mistakes we hit during the first B2/S3 runtime validation cycle.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## A. Runtime materialization\\n\\n- [ ] Every required agent is **really** materialized in OpenClaw runtime\\n- [ ] Every required agent appears in `openclaw agents list`\\n- [ ] Every required agent can execute at least one real turn\\n- [ ] No sector is considered \\\"real\\\" based only on folders/docs existing\\n\\n---\\n\\n## B. Contract freezing\\n\\n- [ ] Canonical input contract exists\\n- [ ] Canonical output contract exists\\n- [ ] Dispatch contract exists\\n- [ ] Resume/reentry contract exists where applicable\\n- [ ] Schema files exist for all outputs that matter\\n- [ ] Version names are aligned (`v1` vs `v2`, etc.)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## C. Invocation primitive\\n\\n- [ ] The exact supervisor -> operator invocation primitive is frozen\\n- [ ] The primitive is proven in this environment\\n- [ ] No ambiguous fallback path remains as the default\\n- [ ] If ACP is mentioned, its role is explicit and non-assumed\\n\\n### Current B2 default lesson\\nFor the current environment, do **not** assume ACP as the default orchestration primitive.\\nPrefer the proven path:\\n\\n```text\\nexec -> openclaw agent --agent <agent_id> --message \\\"...\\\" --json\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## D. Dispatch integrity\\n\\n- [ ] Every operator dispatch file is generated\\n- [ ] Every dispatch path matches the operator expectation\\n- [ ] `operator_name` matches the actual target operator\\n- [ ] `output.output_path` matches the intended runtime location\\n- [ ] Schema id / expected schema matches the operator contract\\n\\n---\\n\\n## E. Operator validation\\n\\n- [ ] Each operator has been run at least once for real\\n- [ ] Runtime success is proven by files, not by conversation alone\\n- [ ] Each operator output was validated against the current canonical schema\\n- [ ] Any legacy output shapes have been normalized or explicitly forbidden\\n- [ ] `status.json` and `checkpoint.json` are written honestly\\n\\n---\\n\\n## F. Supervisor validation\\n\\n- [ ] Supervisor reads bootstrap from disk correctly\\n- [ ] Supervisor writes activation plan correctly\\n- [ ] Supervisor writes dispatches correctly\\n- [ ] Supervisor validates operator artifacts on disk\\n- [ ] Supervisor compile/report/checkpoints are based on real files\\n- [ ] Disk artifacts match what the supervisor claims in chat\\n\\n---\\n\\n## G. Director / block control-plane validation\\n\\n- [ ] Block director active bootstrap is proven\\n- [ ] Block director idempotent/no-op bootstrap is proven\\n- [ ] Block director resume-success path is proven\\n- [ ] Block director resume-failure path is proven (or explicitly deferred)\\n- [ ] `state.json` mutations are verified on disk\\n- [ ] Macro completion/failure checkpoints are verified on disk\\n\\n---\\n\\n## H. Truth model\\n\\n- [ ] Disk is treated as source of truth\\n- [ ] Agent conversational summaries are treated as secondary evidence only\\n- [ ] No completion is accepted without actual persisted artifacts\\n- [ ] `degraded_completed` meaning is explicitly classified:\\n  - [ ] degraded because runtime failed\\n  - [ ] degraded because test scope intentionally ran a subset\\n\\n---\\n\\n## I. Production-mode realism\\n\\n- [ ] Tests are not relying on residual session memory as hidden glue\\n- [ ] Activations are contract-complete and file-driven\\n- [ ] The sector can tolerate fresh activation behavior\\n- [ ] The sector does not depend on thread-bound session mythology\\n\\n---\\n\\n## J. Paperclip / Perseus readiness gate\\n\\nDo **not** let Paperclip rely on a new sector until all of the following are true:\\n\\n- [ ] Director path proven enough for the intended scope\\n- [ ] Supervisor path proven enough for the intended scope\\n- [ ] Required operators proven enough for the intended scope\\n- [ ] Remaining degradation is test-scope only, not infra/runtime failure\\n- [ ] Checkpoint/reentry loop is clear and operational\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Exit question\\n\\nBefore opening the next sector, answer this honestly:\\n\\n> If this sector fails tomorrow, will we know whether it failed because of runtime, dispatch, contract, state transition, or model behavior?\\n\\nIf the answer is **no**, the sector is not preflighted yet.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":220,"output":1074,"cacheRead":162432,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":163726,"cost":{"input":0.00055,"output":0.01611,"cacheRead":0.040608,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.057268}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775240607727,"responseId":"resp_0e086492d0456bb30169d005a0359c81919b7ed0ed7340e35a"}}
