{"type":"message","id":"45374c25","parentId":"6a7fb06d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T18:24:08.213Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_E3SDF2kz0KvCPfoUD7A4kwaf|fc_0e086492d0456bb30169d005c2a3a081918b460069108238e5","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md","edits":[{"oldText":"## 14. Strategic conclusion\n\nThe most important shift from this cycle is that we moved from:\n- vague orchestration ideas\n- runtime ambiguity\n- trust in agent summaries\n\nto:\n- explicit state machines\n- file-based truth\n- validated runtime primitives\n- provable director/supervisor/operator roles\n\nThat shift should now be treated as part of the B2 standard, not as an ad-hoc workaround.\n","newText":"## 14. Strategic conclusion\n\nThe most important shift from this cycle is that we moved from:\n- vague orchestration ideas\n- runtime ambiguity\n- trust in agent summaries\n\nto:\n- explicit state machines\n- file-based truth\n- validated runtime primitives\n- provable director/supervisor/operator roles\n\nThat shift should now be treated as part of the B2 standard, not as an ad-hoc workaround.\n\n---\n\n## 15. Operational consequence\n\nThese learnings were condensed into the reusable preflight document:\n\n- `SECTOR_PREFLIGHT_CHECKLIST.md`\n\nFuture sectors should use that file as the practical gate before asking Paperclip/Perseus to rely on a new sector.\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"## 14. Strategic conclusion\\n\\nThe most important shift from this cycle is that we moved from:\\n- vague orchestration ideas\\n- runtime ambiguity\\n- trust in agent summaries\\n\\nto:\\n- explicit state machines\\n- file-based truth\\n- validated runtime primitives\\n- provable director/supervisor/operator roles\\n\\nThat shift should now be treated as part of the B2 standard, not as an ad-hoc workaround.\\n\",\"newText\":\"## 14. Strategic conclusion\\n\\nThe most important shift from this cycle is that we moved from:\\n- vague orchestration ideas\\n- runtime ambiguity\\n- trust in agent summaries\\n\\nto:\\n- explicit state machines\\n- file-based truth\\n- validated runtime primitives\\n- provable director/supervisor/operator roles\\n\\nThat shift should now be treated as part of the B2 standard, not as an ad-hoc workaround.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 15. Operational consequence\\n\\nThese learnings were condensed into the reusable preflight document:\\n\\n- `SECTOR_PREFLIGHT_CHECKLIST.md`\\n\\nFuture sectors should use that file as the practical gate before asking Paperclip/Perseus to rely on a new sector.\\n\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":184,"output":313,"cacheRead":163584,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":164081,"cost":{"input":0.00046,"output":0.004695,"cacheRead":0.040895999999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.046050999999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775240633765,"responseId":"resp_0e086492d0456bb30169d005ba405c8191bc796cd4fc92068e"}}
