{"type":"message","id":"cc63f657","parentId":"8cbd2029","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:05:17.114Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_LowstwqTU2SiWheiMoEbUPYq|fc_0e086492d0456bb30169d02b7e93848191a09d55f5eb7588b6","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\REPLICATION_GUIDE.md","content":"# Replication Guide for Future Block 2 Sectors\n\n## Purpose\n\nUse this document to replicate the validated S3 pattern in future sectors (S4, S5, S6) without re-living the same weeks of debugging.\n\n---\n\n## Canonical control pattern\n\n```text\nboundary workflow\n  -> b2_director\n    -> {sector}_requested.json\n  -> boundary observes requested checkpoint\n    -> builds sector bootstrap + sector source package\n    -> invokes sector supervisor\n  -> sector supervisor\n    -> activation plan\n    -> dispatches\n    -> operator launches via CLI\n    -> output validation\n    -> compile/report\n    -> sector macro checkpoint\n  -> boundary observes sector macro checkpoint\n    -> builds b2.resume.v1\n    -> reinvokes b2_director\n```\n\n---\n\n## Mandatory rules for a new sector\n\n### 1. Runtime materialization\n- Every agent must appear in `openclaw agents list`\n- Every agent must execute at least one real turn\n\n### 2. Contracts first\nBefore real tests:\n- bootstrap contract\n- resume contract (when applicable)\n- supervisor bootstrap contract\n- operator dispatch contract\n- output schemas\n- macro checkpoint shape\n\n### 3. Invocation primitive\nFor the current environment, default to:\n\n```text\nexec -> openclaw agent --agent <id> --session-id <unique-run-session> --message \"...\" --json --timeout 1800\n```\n\nDo not assume ACP as default orchestration substrate.\n\n### 4. Session hygiene\n- unique `--session-id` per run/stage\n- unique `--session-id` per operator launch\n- do not rely on default CLI session reuse\n\n### 5. Truth model\n- disk artifacts are source of truth\n- chat summaries are secondary\n\n### 6. Path handling\n- paths from bootstrap are literal and canonical\n- no Unicode-normalization heuristics\n- no alternate root discovery\n\n### 7. Macro checkpointing\nA sector must mirror macro status into:\n\n```text\n{b2_root}/checkpoints/{sector}_completed.json\n{b2_root}/checkpoints/{sector}_failed.json\n```\n\n### 8. Director validation\nThe director must validate the paths declared by the sector checkpoint, not assume root-level hardcoded artifacts.\n\n---\n\n## Checklist before opening a new sector\n\n- [ ] director contract for this sector exists\n- [ ] supervisor contract exists\n- [ ] operator registry is closed and explicit\n- [ ] output schemas exist\n- [ ] every operator can run once in runtime real\n- [ ] supervisor can launch operators via CLI\n- [ ] sector compile/report exists\n- [ ] sector macro checkpoint exists\n- [ ] director resume path for this sector is proven\n\n---\n\n## What not to do again\n\n- do not treat ACP as the default answer\n- do not call folder-only agents “ready”\n- do not trust chat summaries over disk\n- do not allow the supervisor to absorb operator semantic work internally\n- do not accept legacy/non-canonical output shapes as “good enough”\n- do not let boundary code work around a broken agent contract if the contract can be fixed at the source\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\REPLICATION_GUIDE.md\",\"content\":\"# Replication Guide for Future Block 2 Sectors\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nUse this document to replicate the validated S3 pattern in future sectors (S4, S5, S6) without re-living the same weeks of debugging.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical control pattern\\n\\n```text\\nboundary workflow\\n  -> b2_director\\n    -> {sector}_requested.json\\n  -> boundary observes requested checkpoint\\n    -> builds sector bootstrap + sector source package\\n    -> invokes sector supervisor\\n  -> sector supervisor\\n    -> activation plan\\n    -> dispatches\\n    -> operator launches via CLI\\n    -> output validation\\n    -> compile/report\\n    -> sector macro checkpoint\\n  -> boundary observes sector macro checkpoint\\n    -> builds b2.resume.v1\\n    -> reinvokes b2_director\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Mandatory rules for a new sector\\n\\n### 1. Runtime materialization\\n- Every agent must appear in `openclaw agents list`\\n- Every agent must execute at least one real turn\\n\\n### 2. Contracts first\\nBefore real tests:\\n- bootstrap contract\\n- resume contract (when applicable)\\n- supervisor bootstrap contract\\n- operator dispatch contract\\n- output schemas\\n- macro checkpoint shape\\n\\n### 3. Invocation primitive\\nFor the current environment, default to:\\n\\n```text\\nexec -> openclaw agent --agent <id> --session-id <unique-run-session> --message \\\"...\\\" --json --timeout 1800\\n```\\n\\nDo not assume ACP as default orchestration substrate.\\n\\n### 4. Session hygiene\\n- unique `--session-id` per run/stage\\n- unique `--session-id` per operator launch\\n- do not rely on default CLI session reuse\\n\\n### 5. Truth model\\n- disk artifacts are source of truth\\n- chat summaries are secondary\\n\\n### 6. Path handling\\n- paths from bootstrap are literal and canonical\\n- no Unicode-normalization heuristics\\n- no alternate root discovery\\n\\n### 7. Macro checkpointing\\nA sector must mirror macro status into:\\n\\n```text\\n{b2_root}/checkpoints/{sector}_completed.json\\n{b2_root}/checkpoints/{sector}_failed.json\\n```\\n\\n### 8. Director validation\\nThe director must validate the paths declared by the sector checkpoint, not assume root-level hardcoded artifacts.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Checklist before opening a new sector\\n\\n- [ ] director contract for this sector exists\\n- [ ] supervisor contract exists\\n- [ ] operator registry is closed and explicit\\n- [ ] output schemas exist\\n- [ ] every operator can run once in runtime real\\n- [ ] supervisor can launch operators via CLI\\n- [ ] sector compile/report exists\\n- [ ] sector macro checkpoint exists\\n- [ ] director resume path for this sector is proven\\n\\n---\\n\\n## What not to do again\\n\\n- do not treat ACP as the default answer\\n- do not call folder-only agents “ready”\\n- do not trust chat summaries over disk\\n- do not allow the supervisor to absorb operator semantic work internally\\n- do not accept legacy/non-canonical output shapes as “good enough”\\n- do not let boundary code work around a broken agent contract if the contract can be fixed at the source\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":172,"output":745,"cacheRead":199296,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":200213,"cost":{"input":0.00043000000000000004,"output":0.011175000000000001,"cacheRead":0.049824,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.061429}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775250298325,"responseId":"resp_0e086492d0456bb30169d02b7b16ec81918e4c106720408016"}}
