{"type":"message","id":"66d335c4","parentId":"14c71ff9","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:05:36.372Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Ad6SbQ09nbtVKwbZPDxjQLOC|fc_0e086492d0456bb30169d02b9175588191bfc2d339c563f8a8","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\CONTRACTS_REGISTRY.md","content":"# Contracts Registry — Block 2 / S3-only validated set\n\n## Purpose\n\nSingle place for the contracts that were actually validated in the first working S3-only E2E.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `b2.bootstrap.v1`\n\n### Purpose\nActivate the B2 director for block bootstrap.\n\n### Required shape\n```json\n{\n  \"kind\": \"b2_start\",\n  \"contract_version\": \"b2.bootstrap.v1\",\n  \"job_id\": \"string\",\n  \"run_root\": \"string\",\n  \"b2_root\": \"string\",\n  \"account_id\": \"string\",\n  \"language\": \"string\",\n  \"inputs\": {\n    \"screenplay_analysis_path\": \"string\"\n  },\n  \"mode\": \"s3_only\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. `b2.resume.v1`\n\n### Purpose\nReactivate the B2 director after a sector event.\n\n### Required shape\n```json\n{\n  \"kind\": \"b2_resume\",\n  \"contract_version\": \"b2.resume.v1\",\n  \"run_root\": \"string\",\n  \"b2_root\": \"string\",\n  \"reason\": \"s3_completed | s3_failed\",\n  \"trigger_artifact\": \"string\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. `s3.supervisor_bootstrap.v1`\n\n### Purpose\nActivate the S3 supervisor with all sector-local runtime roots.\n\n### Required fields\n- `kind = s3_start`\n- `contract_version`\n- `job_id`\n- `video_id`\n- `account_id`\n- `language`\n- `run_root`\n- `sector_root`\n- `source_package_path`\n- `checkpoints_dir`\n- `operators_dir`\n- `compiled_dir`\n- `logs_dir`\n- `dispatch_dir`\n- `bootstrap_checkpoint_path`\n\n---\n\n## 4. `s3.operator_dispatch.v1`\n\n### Purpose\nGive one operator its run-specific execution envelope.\n\n### Required top-level areas\n- execution identity\n- business/job identity\n- semantic context\n- source package path\n- output path + expected schema\n- runtime paths\n- execution policy\n- operator-specific payload\n\n---\n\n## 5. `s3_completed.json`\n\n### Purpose\nMacro block checkpoint signaling that S3 finished successfully enough for the director to resume.\n\n### Required shape\n```json\n{\n  \"event\": \"s3_completed\",\n  \"job_id\": \"string\",\n  \"sector\": \"s3_visual_planning\",\n  \"compiled_entities_path\": \"string\",\n  \"sector_report_path\": \"string\",\n  \"completed_at\": \"ISO_TIMESTAMP\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\"\n}\n```\n\n### Important rule\nThe paths declared here are the source of truth for the director resume validation.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `b2_completed.json`\n\n### Purpose\nMacro block completion artifact for the first S3-only narrow proof.\n\n### Required shape\n```json\n{\n  \"event\": \"b2_completed\",\n  \"job_id\": \"string\",\n  \"mode\": \"s3_only\",\n  \"completed_at\": \"ISO_TIMESTAMP\",\n  \"compiled_entities_path\": \"string\",\n  \"sector_report_path\": \"string\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Practical note\nThese contracts are the validated baseline for future sectors. Extend carefully; do not fork them casually by improvisation in prompts or chat summaries.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\CONTRACTS_REGISTRY.md\",\"content\":\"# Contracts Registry — Block 2 / S3-only validated set\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nSingle place for the contracts that were actually validated in the first working S3-only E2E.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. `b2.bootstrap.v1`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nActivate the B2 director for block bootstrap.\\n\\n### Required shape\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"kind\\\": \\\"b2_start\\\",\\n  \\\"contract_version\\\": \\\"b2.bootstrap.v1\\\",\\n  \\\"job_id\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n  \\\"run_root\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n  \\\"b2_root\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n  \\\"account_id\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n  \\\"language\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n  \\\"inputs\\\": {\\n    \\\"screenplay_analysis_path\\\": \\\"string\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"mode\\\": \\\"s3_only\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2. `b2.resume.v1`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nReactivate the B2 director after a sector event.\\n\\n### Required shape\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"kind\\\": \\\"b2_resume\\\",\\n  \\\"contract_version\\\": \\\"b2.resume.v1\\\",\\n  \\\"run_root\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n  \\\"b2_root\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n  \\\"reason\\\": \\\"s3_completed | s3_failed\\\",\\n  \\\"trigger_artifact\\\": \\\"string\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3. `s3.supervisor_bootstrap.v1`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nActivate the S3 supervisor with all sector-local runtime roots.\\n\\n### Required fields\\n- `kind = s3_start`\\n- `contract_version`\\n- `job_id`\\n- `video_id`\\n- `account_id`\\n- `language`\\n- `run_root`\\n- `sector_root`\\n- `source_package_path`\\n- `checkpoints_dir`\\n- `operators_dir`\\n- `compiled_dir`\\n- `logs_dir`\\n- `dispatch_dir`\\n- `bootstrap_checkpoint_path`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4. `s3.operator_dispatch.v1`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nGive one operator its run-specific execution envelope.\\n\\n### Required top-level areas\\n- execution identity\\n- business/job identity\\n- semantic context\\n- source package path\\n- output path + expected schema\\n- runtime paths\\n- execution policy\\n- operator-specific payload\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 5. `s3_completed.json`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nMacro block checkpoint signaling that S3 finished successfully enough for the director to resume.\\n\\n### Required shape\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"event\\\": \\\"s3_completed\\\",\\n  \\\"job_id\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n  \\\"sector\\\": \\\"s3_visual_planning\\\",\\n  \\\"compiled_entities_path\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n  \\\"sector_report_path\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n  \\\"completed_at\\\": \\\"ISO_TIMESTAMP\\\",\\n  \\\"status\\\": \\\"completed\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Important rule\\nThe paths declared here are the source of truth for the director resume validation.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 6. `b2_completed.json`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nMacro block completion artifact for the first S3-only narrow proof.\\n\\n### Required shape\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"event\\\": \\\"b2_completed\\\",\\n  \\\"job_id\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n  \\\"mode\\\": \\\"s3_only\\\",\\n  \\\"completed_at\\\": \\\"ISO_TIMESTAMP\\\",\\n  \\\"compiled_entities_path\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n  \\\"sector_report_path\\\": \\\"string\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Practical note\\nThese contracts are the validated baseline for future sectors. Extend carefully; do not fork them casually by improvisation in prompts or chat summaries.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":189,"output":844,"cacheRead":200064,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":201097,"cost":{"input":0.00047250000000000005,"output":0.012660000000000001,"cacheRead":0.050016,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0631485}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775250317568,"responseId":"resp_0e086492d0456bb30169d02b8e50e48191be67c8c4cae28849"}}
