{"type":"message","id":"2ed718ef","parentId":"4b8df35e","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:09:00.772Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_JeydWire0iF07j8hLY8DIWEs|fc_0e086492d0456bb30169d02c6994f08191bf044a18771f1764","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_STATE.md:24: > **\"Agora s� falta criar o Perseus no Paperclip.\"**\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_STATE.md:33: **B2 v1 - prepara��o do primeiro teste com S3-only**\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_STATE.md:40: - a limita��o de `sessions_spawn mode=session + thread=true` no WebChat/Control UI foi investigada e considerada fechada em n�vel de diagn�stico\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_STATE.md:153: ### 2. ACP como alternativa\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_STATE.md:218: > **\"Agora s� falta criar o Perseus no Paperclip.\"**\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:30: ## 2. False blocker: ACP as if it were the orchestration substrate\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:33: ACP kept appearing as a blocker when trying to prove `supervisor -> operator` launches.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:36: ACP was **not** the right central runtime for this workflow. The actual viable primitive in this environment is:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:43: We stopped treating ACP as the required execution substrate for S3 orchestration and hard-pinned the supervisor-side runtime path to the CLI primitive above.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:46: - Do not default to ACP for workflow orchestration.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:47: - Treat ACP as optional/auxiliary, not foundational, unless a future sector proves otherwise.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:118: It proved that nested launch did not actually require ACP in the way we had been assuming.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:251: - supervisor drifting into ACP fallback\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:257: - \"the whole architecture is impossible without ACP\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:290: - ACP is the default solution\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\REAL_RUN_VALIDATION_2026-04-03.md:120:   - reason: `ACP runtime backend unavailable; real op_s3_human_subject_extractor session could not be launched.`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\REAL_RUN_VALIDATION_2026-04-03.md:139: 2. Understand why nested real agent launches from `sm_s3_visual_planning` report `ACP runtime backend unavailable`, despite direct top-level operator invocations working from the shell.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\REPLICATION_GUIDE.md:54: Do not assume ACP as default orchestration substrate.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\REPLICATION_GUIDE.md:99: - do not treat ACP as the default answer\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3_POSTMORTEM_AND_PATTERNS.md:41: ### 1. ACP / sessions_spawn as if they were the sector runtime substrate\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3_POSTMORTEM_AND_PATTERNS.md:44: We repeatedly treated ACP or sessions_spawn-like paths as if they were the correct core substrate for `supervisor -> operator` orchestration.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3_POSTMORTEM_AND_PATTERNS.md:54: Supervisor docs and contracts were hardened to treat CLI launch as canonical and ACP as non-primary for this hop.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3_POSTMORTEM_AND_PATTERNS.md:127: - supervisor regressed to ACP / subset execution\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3_POSTMORTEM_AND_PATTERNS.md:165: CLI > ACP for current supervisor -> operator orchestration.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\SECTOR_PREFLIGHT_CHECKLIST.md:34: - [ ] If ACP is mentioned, its role is explicit and non-assumed\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\SECTOR_PREFLIGHT_CHECKLIST.md:37: For the current environment, do **not** assume ACP as the default orchestration primitive.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\runtime_realcheck\\run_005\\b2\\sectors\\s3_visual_planning\\checkpoints\\s3_final_checkpoint.json:10:     \"ACP runtime backend unavailable; real op_s3_human_subject_extractor session could not be launched.\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\runtime_realcheck\\run_005\\b2\\sectors\\s3_visual_planning\\operators\\human_subject_extractor\\output.json:52:     \"Operator agent could not be invoked because ACP runtime backend is not configured in this environment; output was produced by supervisor fallback for validation continuity.\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\runtime_realcheck\\run_005\\b2\\sectors\\s3_visual_planning\\operators\\human_subject_extractor\\status.json:6:   \"note\": \"Validated structurally; operator ag