{"type":"message","id":"82d89d5d","parentId":"eea6cd22","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:09:12.145Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ICcUr3hbmJ53FVhvGS2zFeXP|fc_0e086492d0456bb30169d02c76d6b481918f73223dd98ad571","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# EXECUTION_STATE.md �?\" Content Factory Block 2\r\n\r\n## Objectivo\r\n\r\nEste documento regista o estado vivo de execu��ǜo do plano do Bloco 2.\r\n\r\nAo contrǭrio do `EXECUTION_PLAN.md`, que define estratǸgia, escopo e sequǦncia, este ficheiro existe para responder:\r\n\r\n- onde estamos agora\r\n- o que jǭ foi materializado\r\n- o que ainda falta\r\n- qual Ǹ o pr��ximo passo exacto\r\n- quais blockers ou dǧvidas estǜo activos\r\n- qual Ǹ a milestone actual de paragem\r\n\r\nEste ficheiro deve permitir retomar a execu��ǜo do programa mesmo ap��s pausas, reentradas ou mudan��as de sessǜo.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Milestone alvo actual\r\n\r\nChegar ao ponto em que Tobias possa dizer ao Lucca:\r\n\r\n> **\"Agora s�� falta criar o Perseus no Paperclip.\"**\r\n\r\nIsto significa deixar o lado OpenClaw do B2 suficientemente constru��do, coerente e revisǭvel para que a pr��xima pe��a cr��tica seja a cria��ǜo/integra��ǜo do agente Perseus no lado Paperclip.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Estado actual resumido\r\n\r\n### Fase do programa\r\n**B2 v1 �?\" prepara��ǜo do primeiro teste com S3-only**\r\n\r\n### Situa��ǜo geral\r\n- a arquitectura do B2 foi desenhada e documentada\r\n- o S3 foi profundamente destrinchado e documentado\r\n- o `b2_director` foi conceptualizado e parcialmente materializado como workspace local\r\n- existe um plano-mǜe de execu��ǜo (`EXECUTION_PLAN.md`)\r\n- a limita��ǜo de `sessions_spawn mode=session + thread=true` no WebChat/Control UI foi investigada e considerada fechada em n��vel de diagn��stico\r\n\r\n### Conclusǜo operacional actual\r\nO modelo correcto para o B2 no ambiente actual Ǹ:\r\n- **state machine com reentradas discretas**\r\n- **estado persistido em disco**\r\n- **execu��ǜo baseada em `mode: run`** para activa����es discretas\r\n- **sem dependǦncia de thread-bound persistent subagent sessions**\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## O que jǭ foi criado / documentado\r\n\r\n### Bloco 2\r\nEm `content_factory_block2/`:\r\n\r\n- `B2_runtime_control_flow.md`\r\n- `B2_director.md`\r\n- `EXECUTION_PLAN.md`\r\n- `EXECUTION_STATE.md` (este ficheiro)\r\n\r\n### S3\r\nEm `content_factory_block2/S3/`:\r\n\r\n- `inputs.md`\r\n- `architecture.md`\r\n- `workflow_bootstrap.md`\r\n- `supervisor.md`\r\n- `operators.md`\r\n- `runtime_layout.md`\r\n- `post_dispatch.md`\r\n\r\n### Agent jǭ materializado\r\nEm `.openclaw/agents/`:\r\n\r\n- `b2_director/`\r\n  - `IDENTITY.md`\r\n  - `MISSION.md`\r\n  - `CONTEXT.md`\r\n  - `CONTRACT.md`\r\n  - `OPERATIONS.md`\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## O que ainda falta criar\r\n\r\n### Contracts centrais do S3\r\n**Jǭ materializados oficialmente:**\r\n\r\n- `S3/contracts/operator_dispatch_contract.md`\r\n- `S3/contracts/operator_registry.md`\r\n- `S3/contracts/supervisor_bootstrap_contract.md`\r\n\r\n### Schemas do S3\r\n**Jǭ materializados oficialmente:**\r\n\r\n- `S3/schemas/human_subject_output.schema.json`\r\n- `S3/schemas/environment_location_output.schema.json`\r\n- `S3/schemas/object_artifact_output.schema.json`\r\n- `S3/schemas/symbolic_event_output.schema.json`\r\n- `S3/schemas/compiled_entities.schema.json`\r\n\r\n### Agents oficiais do S3\r\n**Jǭ criados oficialmente:**\r\n\r\n- `sm_s3_visual_planning`\r\n- `op_s3_human_subject_extractor`\r\n- `op_s3_environment_location_extractor`\r\n- `op_s3_object_artifact_extractor`\r\n- `op_s3_symbolic_event_extractor`\r\n\r\n### Helpers / substrate m��nimos\r\n**Criados oficialmente:**\r\n\r\n- `S3/helpers/validate_operator_output.py`\r\n- `S3/helpers/compile_s3_entities.py`\r\n- `S3/helpers/generate_s3_sector_report.py`\r\n- `helpers/b2_state_helper.py`\r\n- `helpers/build_s3_bootstrap_from_b2.py`\r\n- `helpers/dry_run_b2_s3_only.py`\r\n\r\n**Ainda por criar/refinar:**\r\n\r\n- wiring real de invoca��ǜo supervisor -> operators\r\n- wiring real de reconhecimento `b2_director -> S3 checkpoints` dentro de activa����es reais de agents\r\n- boundary prǭtica Paperclip/Perseus para fora do dry run\r\n\r\n### Integra��ǜo prǭtica B2 -> S3\r\n**Fechada estruturalmente / parcialmente provada em dry run:**\r\n\r\n- modo de activa��ǜo do `sm_s3_visual_planning` pelo `b2_director` definido documentalmente\r\n- checkpoint de conclusǜo/falha do S3 em formato v1 definido\r\n- comportamento exacto do B2 no primeiro teste S3-only definido\r\n- dry run estrutural m��nimo executado com sucesso em `runtime_dryrun/run_001/`\r\n\r\n**Ainda falta:**\r\n- substituir a simula��ǜo pelos turns reais dos agents (`b2_director` / `sm_s3_visual_planning` / operators)\r\n\r\n### Perseus / Paperclip\r\nAinda nǜo tratado em detalhe de implementa��ǜo.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Dǧvidas / blockers activos\r\n\r\n### 1. Thread-bound persistent subagent sessions no WebChat\r\n**Status:** diagnosticado / considerado fechado\r\n\r\nConclusǜo actual:\r\n- nǜo suportado hoje para subagents normais no WebChat/Control UI/Nerve\r\n- nǜo bloquear o B2 por causa disso\r\n- usar persistǦncia baseada em estado + sess��es/cron/tasks, nǜo em thread binding\r\n\r\n### 2. ACP como alternativa\r\n**Status:** hip��tese futura / nǜo necessǭria para esta fase\r\n\r\nNǜo Ǹ dependǦncia do B2 v1.\r\n\r\n### 3. Forma exacta da continuidade aut��noma do Tobias enquanto Lucca estǭ fora\r\n**Status:** em desenho operacional\r\n\r\nPr��ximo passo: definir cron + sessǜo nomeada persistente e limites/compaction.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Pr��ximos passos exactos\r\n\r\n### Passo imediato 1\r\nDefinir a forma exacta de continuidade operacional do Tobias enquanto o Lucca estǭ fora:\r\n- sessǜo nomeada persistente\r\n- cron\r\n- cadǦncia\r\n- stop condition\r\n- delivery policy\r\n- comportamento de contexto/compaction\r\n\r\n### Passo imediato 2\r\nSubstituir o dry run simulado por activa����es reais dos agents do B2/S3.\r\n\r\n### Passo imediato 3\r\nDefinir a boundary operacional m��nima do primeiro teste S3-only do lado Paperclip/Perseus.\r\n\r\n### Passo imediato 4\r\nFazer o primeiro run narrow com agents reais e artefactos persistidos.\r\n\r\n### Passo imediato 5\r\nS�� depois expandir para wiring mais completo e prepara��ǜo de S4.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Regra operacional de execu��ǜo\r\n\r\nDurante esta fase, a execu��ǜo deve manter foco estrito em:\r\n\r\n- B2 v1\r\n- S3-only para o primeiro teste\r\n- GPT-5.4 mini via OpenAI OAuth para todos os agents desta fase\r\n- contexto limpo por activa��ǜo\r\n- estado persistido no disco como fonte de verdade\r\n\r\nNǜo expandir para S4/S5/S6 antes de o S3 e o runtime do B2 estarem coerentes o suficiente para revisǜo e integra��ǜo com Perseus.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## CritǸrio de paragem desta fase aut��noma\r\n\r\nEsta fase de execu��ǜo aut��noma deve parar quando o estado atingir algo equivalente a:\r\n\r\n- contracts do S3 criados\r\n- schemas do S3 criados\r\n- agents do S3 criados\r\n- helpers m��nimos criados\r\n- `b2_director` ligado ao S3\r\n- estado/documenta��ǜo suficientemente claros para revisǜo humana\r\n- o pr��ximo elo cr��tico passar a ser a cria��ǜo do **Perseus** no Paperclip\r\n\r\nNesse momento, a mensagem esperada ao Lucca Ǹ:\r\n\r\n> **\"Agora s�� falta criar o Perseus no Paperclip.\"**"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":341,"aggregated":"# EXECUTION_STATE.md �?\" Content Factory Block 2\r\n\r\n## Objectivo\r\n\r\nEste documento regista o estado vivo de execu��ǜo do plano do Bloco 2.\r\n\r\nAo contrǭrio do `EXECUTION_PLAN.md`, que define estratǸgia, escopo e sequǦncia, este ficheiro existe para responder:\r\n\r\n- onde estamos agora\r\n- o que jǭ foi materializado\r\n- o que ainda falta\r\n- qual Ǹ o pr��ximo passo exacto\r\n- quais blockers ou dǧvidas estǜo activos\r\n- qual Ǹ a milestone actual de paragem\r\n\r\nEste ficheiro deve permitir retomar a execu��ǜo do programa mesmo ap��s pausas, reentradas ou mudan��as de sessǜo.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Milestone alvo actual\r\n\r\nChegar ao ponto em que Tobias possa dizer ao Lucca:\r\n\r\n> **\"Agora s�� falta criar o Perseus no Paperclip.\"**\r\n\r\nIsto significa deixar o lado OpenClaw do B2 suficientemente constru��do, coerente e revisǭvel para que a pr��xima pe��a cr��tica seja a cria��ǜo/integra��ǜo do agente Perseus no lado Paperclip.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Estado actual resumido\r\n\r\n### Fase do programa\r\n**B2 v1 �?\" prepara��ǜo do primeiro teste com S3-only**\r\n\r\n### Situa��ǜo geral\r\n- a arquitectura do B2 foi desenhada e documentada\r\n- o S3 foi profundamente destrinchado e documentado\r\n- o `b2_director` foi conceptualizado e parcialmente materializado como workspace local\r\n- existe um plano-mǜe de execu��ǜo (`EXECUTION_PLAN.md`)\r\n- a limita��ǜo de `sessions_spawn mode=session + thread=true` no WebChat/Control UI foi investigada e considerada fechada em n��vel de diagn��stico\r\n\r\n### Conclusǜo operacional actual\r\nO modelo correcto para o B2 no ambiente actual Ǹ:\r\n- **state machine com reentradas discretas**\r\n- **estado persistido em disco**\r\n- **execu��ǜo baseada em `mode: run`** para activa����es discretas\r\n- **sem dependǦncia de thread-bound persistent subagent sessions**\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## O que jǭ foi criado / documentado\r\n\r\n### Bloco 2\r\nEm `content_factory_block2/`:\r\n\r\n- `B2_runtime_control_flow.md`\r\n- `B2_director.md`\r\n- `EXECUTION_PLAN.md`\r\n- `EXECUTION_STATE.md` (este ficheiro)\r\n\r\n### S3\r\nEm `content_factory_block2/S3/`:\r\n\r\n- `inputs.md`\r\n- `architecture.md`\r\n- `workflow_bootstrap.md`\r\n- `supervisor.md`\r\n- `operators.md`\r\n- `runtime_layout.md`\r\n- `post_dispatch.md`\r\n\r\n### Agent jǭ materializado\r\nEm `.openclaw/agents/`:\r\n\r\n- `b2_director/`\r\n  - `IDENTITY.md`\r\n  - `MISSION.md`\r\n  - `CONTEXT.md`\r\n  - `CONTRACT.md`\r\n  - `OPERATIONS.md`\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## O que ainda falta criar\r\n\r\n### Contracts centrais do S3\r\n**Jǭ materializados oficialmente:**\r\n\r\n- `S3/contracts/operator_dispatch_contract.md`\r\n- `S3/contracts/operator_registry.md`\r\n- `S3/contracts/supervisor_bootstrap_contract.md`\r\n\r\n### Schemas do S3\r\n**Jǭ materializados oficialmente:**\r\n\r\n- `S3/schemas/human_subject_output.schema.json`\r\n- `S3/schemas/environment_location_output.schema.json`\r\n- `S3/schemas/object_artifact_output.schema.json`\r\n- `S3/schemas/symbolic_event_output.schema.json`\r\n- `S3/schemas/compiled_entities.schema.json`\r\n\r\n### Agents oficiais do S3\r\n**Jǭ criados oficialmente:**\r\n\r\n- `sm_s3_visual_planning`\r\n- `op_s3_human_subject_extractor`\r\n- `op_s3_environment_location_extractor`\r\n- `op_s3_object_artifact_extractor`\r\n- `op_s3_symbolic_event_extractor`\r\n\r\n### Helpers / substrate m��nimos\r\n**Criados oficialmente:**\r\n\r\n- `S3/helpers/validate_operator_output.py`\r\n- `S3/helpers/compile_s3_entities.py`\r\n- `S3/helpers/generate_s3_sector_report.py`\r\n- `helpers/b2_state_helper.py`\r\n- `helpers/build_s3_bootstrap_from_b2.py`\r\n- `helpers/dry_run_b2_s3_only.py`\r\n\r\n**Ainda por criar/refinar:**\r\n\r\n- wiring real de invoca��ǜo supervisor -> operators\r\n- wiring real de reconhecimento `b2_director -> S3 checkpoints` dentro de activa����es reais de agents\r\n- boundary prǭtica Paperclip/Perseus para fora do dry run\r\n\r\n### Integra��ǜo prǭtica B2 -> S3\r\n**Fechada estruturalmente / parcialmente provada em dry run:**\r\n\r\n- modo de activa��ǜo do `sm_s3_visual_planning` pelo `b2_director` definido documentalmente\r\n- checkpoint de conclusǜo/falha do S3 em formato v1 definido\r\n- comportamento exacto do B2 no primeiro teste S3-only definido\r\n- dry run estrutural m��nimo executado com sucesso em `runtime_dryrun/run_001/`\r\n\r\n**Ainda falta:**\r\n- substituir a simula��ǜo pelos turns reais dos agents (`b2_director` / `sm_s3_visual_planning` / operators)\r\n\r\n### Perseus / Paperclip\r\nAinda nǜo tratado em detalhe de implementa��ǜo.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Dǧvidas / blockers activos\r\n\r\n### 1. Thread-bound persistent subagent sessions no WebChat\r\n**Status:** diagnosticado / considerado fechado\r\n\r\nConclusǜo actual:\r\n- nǜo suportado hoje para subagents normais no WebChat/Control UI/Nerve\r\n- nǜo bloquear o B2 por causa disso\r\n- usar persistǦncia baseada em estado + sess��es/cron/tasks, nǜo em thread binding\r\n\r\n### 2. ACP como alternativa\r\n**Status:** hip��tese futura / nǜo necessǭria para esta fase\r\n\r\nNǜo Ǹ dependǦncia do B2 v1.\r\n\r\n### 3. Forma exacta da continuidade aut��noma do Tobias enquanto Lucca estǭ fora\r\n**Status:** em desenho operacional\r\n\r\nPr��ximo passo: definir cron + sessǜo nomeada persistente e limites/compaction.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Pr��ximos passos exactos\r\n\r\n### Passo imediato 1\r\nDefinir a forma exacta de continuidade operacional do Tobias enquanto o Lucca estǭ fora:\r\n- sessǜo nomeada persistente\r\n- cron\r\n- cadǦncia\r\n- stop condition\r\n- delivery policy\r\n- comportamento de contexto/compaction\r\n\r\n### Passo imediato 2\r\nSubstituir o dry run simulado por activa����es reais dos agents do B2/S3.\r\n\r\n### Passo imediato 3\r\nDefinir a boundary operacional m��nima do primeiro teste S3-only do lado Paperclip/Perseus.\r\n\r\n### Passo imediato 4\r\nFazer o primeiro run narrow com agents reais e artefactos persistidos.\r\n\r\n### Passo imediato 5\r\nS�� depois expandir para wiring mais completo e prepara��ǜo de S4.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Regra operacional de execu��ǜo\r\n\r\nDurante esta fase, a execu��ǜo deve manter foco estrito em:\r\n\r\n- B2 v1\r\n- S3-only para o primeiro teste\r\n- GPT-5.4 mini via OpenAI OAuth para todos os agents desta fase\r\n- contexto limpo por activa��ǜo\r\n- estado persistido no disco como fonte de verdade\r\n\r\nNǜo expandir para S4/S5/S6 antes de o S3 e o runtime do B2 estarem coerentes o suficiente para revisǜo e integra��ǜo com Perseus.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## CritǸrio de paragem desta fase aut��noma\r\n\r\nEsta fase de execu��ǜo aut��noma deve parar quando o estado atingir algo equivalente a:\r\n\r\n- contracts do S3 criados\r\n- schemas do S3 criados\r\n- agents do S3 criados\r\n- helpers m��nimos criados\r\n- `b2_director` ligado ao S3\r\n- estado/documenta��ǜo suficientemente claros para revisǜo humana\r\n- o pr��ximo elo cr��tico passar a ser a cria��ǜo do **Perseus** no Paperclip\r\n\r\nNesse momento, a mensagem esperada ao Lucca Ǹ:\r\n\r\n> **\"Agora s�� falta criar o Perseus no Paperclip.\"**","cwd":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775250552079}}
{"type":"message","id":"e63f7e92","parentId":"82d89d5d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:09:44.102Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"O `EXECUTION_STATE.md` ainda estava cheio de resquícios antigos e até encoding quebrado. Vou substituir esse ficheiro por uma versão limpa, coerente com o estado real pós-E2E, em vez de fazer remendos locais.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e086492d0456bb30169d02c7cfcb08191876d3822a0ec4de2\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_JclUJUs1fW3lC7EvKp6bMRRw|fc_0e086492d0456bb30169d02c7e2ba08191a85908a246cc4864","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_STATE.md","content":"# EXECUTION_STATE.md — Content Factory Block 2\n\n## Objective\n\nThis document tracks the live execution state of Block 2.\n\nUnlike `EXECUTION_PLAN.md`, which defines strategy and sequencing, this file exists to answer:\n\n- where we are now\n- what has already been materially proven\n- what is already stable enough to reuse\n- what remains open\n- what the next exact step is\n\n---\n\n## Current milestone\n\nThe first narrow **S3-only E2E** for Block 2 is now **validated**.\n\nThe current milestone is no longer “reach Perseus readiness”.\nIt is now:\n\n> consolidate the validated pattern so S4/S5/S6 can be opened with far less ambiguity, less debugging, and less wasted time.\n\n---\n\n## Current state summary\n\n### Program phase\n**B2 v1 — S3-only E2E narrow validated; current phase = consolidation and replication**\n\n### General situation\n- the B2 architecture is documented\n- the S3 architecture is documented\n- `b2_director` is materialized and proven in runtime real\n- `sm_s3_visual_planning` is materialized and proven in runtime real\n- the 4 S3 operators are materialized and proven in runtime real\n- the first Paperclip-side E2E narrow flow succeeded from boundary bootstrap to `b2_completed.json`\n\n### Operational conclusion\nThe correct model for Block 2 in the current environment is:\n- state machine with discrete reentries\n- persisted state and checkpoints on disk\n- boundary-driven observation and reactivation\n- no dependence on thread-bound persistent sessions\n- CLI primitive for the current `supervisor -> operator` hop\n\n---\n\n## What is now materially proven\n\n### B2 director\nProven in runtime real for:\n- active bootstrap\n- idempotent/no-op bootstrap\n- resume on `s3_completed`\n- writing `b2_completed.json` in `mode = s3_only`\n\n### S3 supervisor\nProven in runtime real for:\n- bootstrap ingestion\n- activation plan generation\n- dispatch generation\n- sector-local compiled artifacts\n- macro checkpoint emission requirement\n- role as sector supervisor in the validated E2E chain\n\n### S3 operators\nThe following were all proven in real runs:\n- `op_s3_human_subject_extractor`\n- `op_s3_environment_location_extractor`\n- `op_s3_object_artifact_extractor`\n- `op_s3_symbolic_event_extractor`\n\n### Paperclip/OpenClaw boundary flow\nValidated narrow pattern:\n\n```text\nw3_block2.py\n  -> b2_director bootstrap\n  -> s3_requested.json\n  -> boundary observes request and launches S3 supervisor\n  -> supervisor + operator layer\n  -> s3_completed.json\n  -> boundary observes completion and reinvokes b2_director\n  -> b2_completed.json\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key validated runtime rules\n\n### 1. Truth model\nDisk artifacts are the operational source of truth.\nChat summaries are secondary.\n\n### 2. Director handoff rule\n`b2_director` must validate the paths declared in `s3_completed.json`, not assume root-level hardcoded artifacts.\n\n### 3. Supervisor/operator primitive\nThe current validated primitive is:\n\n```text\nexec -> openclaw agent --agent <operator_id> --session-id <unique-run-operator-session> --message \"...\" --json --timeout 1800\n```\n\n### 4. Session hygiene\nDefault CLI session reuse is not acceptable as a production assumption.\nUse unique `session-id` values per run/stage/operator.\n\n### 5. Canonical operator model\nThe S3 supervisor must treat the operator registry as closed for the current phase:\n- human_subject_extractor\n- environment_location_extractor\n- object_artifact_extractor\n- symbolic_event_extractor\n\nThe supervisor must not substitute internal semantic work for those operator dispatches.\n\n---\n\n## Active consolidation tasks\n\n### 1. Documentation consolidation\nCreate/update the central docs that turn S3 learnings into reusable engineering pattern:\n- `S3_POSTMORTEM_AND_PATTERNS.md`\n- `REPLICATION_GUIDE.md`\n- `CONTRACTS_REGISTRY.md`\n- `SECTOR_PREFLIGHT_CHECKLIST.md`\n- `POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md`\n- `EXECUTION_PLAN.md`\n- `EXECUTION_STATE.md`\n\n### 2. Session hygiene hardening\nThe pattern for clean per-run activation is understood but must remain an explicit engineering rule in future sectors.\n\n### 3. Next-sector readiness\nBefore opening S4, the validated S3 pattern should be treated as the baseline and checked through the official sector preflight checklist.\n\n---\n\n## What is no longer an active blocker\n\n### ACP as central orchestration substrate\nNo longer treated as the solution path for this block.\n\n### “Agent exists because folder exists” confusion\nResolved by runtime materialization and real-run validation.\n\n### Director viability\nResolved for the validated S3-only narrow path.\n\n### Basic Paperclip/OpenClaw viability\nResolved for the first narrow E2E path.\n\n---\n\n## What remains open\n\n### 1. Production-hardening across many sequential videos\nThe pattern works, but repeated production use still requires discipline on session hygiene, cleanup, and run isolation.\n\n### 2. Replication to S4/S5/S6\nStill open. The goal now is to avoid re-learning the same runtime lessons sector by sector.\n\n### 3. Full multi-sector block behavior\nOnly the S3-only narrow path is validated. The full S3 -> S4 -> S5 -> S6 chain is not yet proven.\n\n---\n\n## Next exact step\n\n### Immediate next step\nFinish consolidating the validated S3 pattern into reusable documentation and execution guidance so the next sector can be opened under a much tighter engineering process.\n\n### After that\nUse `SECTOR_PREFLIGHT_CHECKLIST.md` before opening S4.\n\n---\n\n## Stop condition for this consolidation phase\n\nThis consolidation phase is complete when:\n- the validated S3 runtime pattern is clearly documented\n- execution docs reflect the real post-E2E state\n- contracts are registered in one place\n- future-sector preflight is operationalized\n- the next sector can start from a reusable, explicit baseline instead of ad-hoc troubleshooting\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\EXECUTION_STATE.md\",\"content\":\"# EXECUTION_STATE.md — Content Factory Block 2\\n\\n## Objective\\n\\nThis document tracks the live execution state of Block 2.\\n\\nUnlike `EXECUTION_PLAN.md`, which defines strategy and sequencing, this file exists to answer:\\n\\n- where we are now\\n- what has already been materially proven\\n- what is already stable enough to reuse\\n- what remains open\\n- what the next exact step is\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Current milestone\\n\\nThe first narrow **S3-only E2E** for Block 2 is now **validated**.\\n\\nThe current milestone is no longer “reach Perseus readiness”.\\nIt is now:\\n\\n> consolidate the validated pattern so S4/S5/S6 can be opened with far less ambiguity, less debugging, and less wasted time.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Current state summary\\n\\n### Program phase\\n**B2 v1 — S3-only E2E narrow validated; current phase = consolidation and replication**\\n\\n### General situation\\n- the B2 architecture is documented\\n- the S3 architecture is documented\\n- `b2_director` is materialized and proven in runtime real\\n- `sm_s3_visual_planning` is materialized and proven in runtime real\\n- the 4 S3 operators are materialized and proven in runtime real\\n- the first Paperclip-side E2E narrow flow succeeded from boundary bootstrap to `b2_completed.json`\\n\\n### Operational conclusion\\nThe correct model for Block 2 in the current environment is:\\n- state machine with discrete reentries\\n- persisted state and checkpoints on disk\\n- boundary-driven observation and reactivation\\n- no dependence on thread-bound persistent sessions\\n- CLI primitive for the current `supervisor -> operator` hop\\n\\n---\\n\\n## What is now materially proven\\n\\n### B2 director\\nProven in runtime real for:\\n- active bootstrap\\n- idempotent/no-op bootstrap\\n- resume on `s3_completed`\\n- writing `b2_completed.json` in `mode = s3_only`\\n\\n### S3 supervisor\\nProven in runtime real for:\\n- bootstrap ingestion\\n- activation plan generation\\n- dispatch generation\\n- sector-local compiled artifacts\\n- macro checkpoint emission requirement\\n- role as sector supervisor in the validated E2E chain\\n\\n### S3 operators\\nThe following were all proven in real runs:\\n- `op_s3_human_subject_extractor`\\n- `op_s3_environment_location_extractor`\\n- `op_s3_object_artifact_extractor`\\n- `op_s3_symbolic_event_extractor`\\n\\n### Paperclip/OpenClaw boundary flow\\nValidated narrow pattern:\\n\\n```text\\nw3_block2.py\\n  -> b2_director bootstrap\\n  -> s3_requested.json\\n  -> boundary observes request and launches S3 supervisor\\n  -> supervisor + operator layer\\n  -> s3_completed.json\\n  -> boundary observes completion and reinvokes b2_director\\n  -> b2_completed.json\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Key validated runtime rules\\n\\n### 1. Truth model\\nDisk artifacts are the operational source of truth.\\nChat summaries are secondary.\\n\\n### 2. Director handoff rule\\n`b2_director` must validate the paths declared in `s3_completed.json`, not assume root-level hardcoded artifacts.\\n\\n### 3. Supervisor/operator primitive\\nThe current validated primitive is:\\n\\n```text\\nexec -> openclaw agent --agent <operator_id> --session-id <unique-run-operator-session> --message \\\"...\\\" --json --timeout 1800\\n```\\n\\n### 4. Session hygiene\\nDefault CLI session reuse is not acceptable as a production assumption.\\nUse unique `session-id` values per run/stage/operator.\\n\\n### 5. Canonical operator model\\nThe S3 supervisor must treat the operator registry as closed for the current phase:\\n- human_subject_extractor\\n- environment_location_extractor\\n- object_artifact_extractor\\n- symbolic_event_extractor\\n\\nThe supervisor must not substitute internal semantic work for those operator dispatches.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Active consolidation tasks\\n\\n### 1. Documentation consolidation\\nCreate/update the central docs that turn S3 learnings into reusable engineering pattern:\\n- `S3_POSTMORTEM_AND_PATTERNS.md`\\n- `REPLICATION_GUIDE.md`\\n- `CONTRACTS_REGISTRY.md`\\n- `SECTOR_PREFLIGHT_CHECKLIST.md`\\n- `POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md`\\n- `EXECUTION_PLAN.md`\\n- `EXECUTION_STATE.md`\\n\\n### 2. Session hygiene hardening\\nThe pattern for clean per-run activation is understood but must remain an explicit engineering rule in future sectors.\\n\\n### 3. Next-sector readiness\\nBefore opening S4, the validated S3 pattern should be treated as the baseline and checked through the official sector preflight checklist.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## What is no longer an active blocker\\n\\n### ACP as central orchestration substrate\\nNo longer treated as the solution path for this block.\\n\\n### “Agent exists because folder exists” confusion\\nResolved by runtime materialization and real-run validation.\\n\\n### Director viability\\nResolved for the validated S3-only narrow path.\\n\\n### Basic Paperclip/OpenClaw viability\\nResolved for the first narrow E2E path.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## What remains open\\n\\n### 1. Production-hardening across many sequential videos\\nThe pattern works, but repeated production use still requires discipline on session hygiene, cleanup, and run isolation.\\n\\n### 2. Replication to S4/S5/S6\\nStill open. The goal now is to avoid re-learning the same runtime lessons sector by sector.\\n\\n### 3. Full multi-sector block behavior\\nOnly the S3-only narrow path is validated. The full S3 -> S4 -> S5 -> S6 chain is not yet proven.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Next exact step\\n\\n### Immediate next step\\nFinish consolidating the validated S3 pattern into reusable documentation and execution guidance so the next sector can be opened under a much tighter engineering process.\\n\\n### After that\\nUse `SECTOR_PREFLIGHT_CHECKLIST.md` before opening S4.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Stop condition for this consolidation phase\\n\\nThis consolidation phase is complete when:\\n- the validated S3 runtime pattern is clearly documented\\n- execution docs reflect the real post-E2E state\\n- contracts are registered in one place\\n- future-sector preflight is operationalized\\n- the next sector can start from a reusable, explicit baseline instead of ad-hoc troubleshooting\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":6808,"output":1515,"cacheRead":190976,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":199299,"cost":{"input":0.01702,"output":0.022725000000000002,"cacheRead":0.047743999999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.087489}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775250552148,"responseId":"resp_0e086492d0456bb30169d02c78e67c8191a2185e86c904fd3b"}}
