{"type":"message","id":"4cd8e3dd","parentId":"f1167195","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:36:38.807Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_HFPavdOpubKbUH0ga2xoJN2x|fc_0e086492d0456bb30169d032e3569481919a67ebc7bae24c12","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:3: description: Plan and implement a new Block 2 sector (such as S4, S5, S6, or a future visual-production sector) using the validated S3 pattern. Use when opening a new Block 2 sector from scratch, defining its architecture/contracts/schemas/supervisor/operators/runtime layout, materializing the corresponding OpenClaw agents, validating them in runtime real, and preparing the sector for Paperclip/Perseus integration without repeating the failures from S3.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:30: If Claude Code has already produced Paperclip-side integration docs for the same cycle (for example `docs/openclaw_integration.md` in the Auto Content Factory repo), read them too to keep both sides of the boundary aligned.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:127: exec -> openclaw agent --agent <operator_id> --session-id <unique-run-operator-session> --message \"...\" --json --timeout 1800\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:131: - do not use ACP/sessions_spawn as primary orchestration path\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:136: - write the macro checkpoint into `b2/checkpoints/`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:182: - required absolute artifact paths (for example `compiled_entities_path`, `sector_report_path`)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:235: - CLI is the invocation primitive, not ACP/sessions_spawn for this hop\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:236: - `--session-id` is unique per run/operator\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:237: - `--timeout 1800` is explicit for operator launches\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:239: - no references to `auto_content_factory_legacy`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:240: - macro checkpoint must be mirrored in `b2/checkpoints/`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:262: ### Lesson: ACP/sessions_spawn is not the default orchestration primitive\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:263: Use CLI.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:266: Use unique `--session-id` per run and per operator.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:280: ### Lesson: macro checkpoints are mandatory\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:290: Use `--timeout 1800` explicitly for supervisor -> operator CLI launches.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:293: ### Lesson: `degraded_completed` is not acceptable as the target state for validated sector closure\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:310: - each operator runs once by manual CLI invoke\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:319: - writes macro checkpoint\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:326: - boundary -> director -> supervisor -> operators -> macro checkpoint -> director resume -> block checkpoint\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:336: - [ ] no docs reference `auto_content_factory_legacy`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:337: - [ ] CLI dispatch pattern is explicit with `--session-id` and `--timeout 1800`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:339: - [ ] macro checkpoint shape includes absolute artifact paths\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\block2-new-sector\\SKILL.md:352: ## 13. Handoff to Claude Code / Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\B2_contracts.md:88:   \"compiled_entities_path\": \"C:/.../compiled/compiled_entities.json\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\B2_contracts.md:89:   \"sector_report_path\": \"C:/.../compiled/s3_sector_report.md\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\B2_director.md:12: - rela��o com Paperclip / boundary workflow / supervisores sectoriais\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\B2_director.md:41: - o boundary com o Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\B2_director.md:94: - substituir o boundary workflow com o Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\B2_director.md:101: ### Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\B2_director.md:103: O Paperclip n�o conversa directamente com o interior do B2.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\B2_director.md:134: No lado Paperclip, o agent respons�vel por activar e monitorar o Bloco 2 foi nomeado como **Perseus**.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\B2_director.md:138: - **Perseus** -> actor Paperclip-facing\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\B2_director.md:257: Mais tarde pode surgir um estado como `degraded_completed`, se for necess�rio.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\B2_director.md:296: - v