rs\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:24: > construir a primeira vers�o execut�vel e test�vel do Bloco 2 com foco inicial em **S3 only**, validando a integra��o real entre Paperclip e OpenClaw.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:31: Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:42: Provar que o B2 pode ser activado do lado Paperclip, entrar no OpenClaw, executar o S3 completo com agents reais, produzir os artefactos esperados, encerrar o sector correctamente e dar sinais compat�veis com o runtime macro do B2.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:52: - integra��o Paperclip -> Perseus -> boundary B2 -> OpenClaw\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:98: ### 1. O Bloco 2 � uma unidade paperclip-facing �nica\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:100: O Paperclip n�o deve orquestrar S3, S4, S5 e S6 sector a sector.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:102: O Paperclip deve ver o B2 como uma unidade �nica.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:114: O Paperclip conversa com uma boundary surface do B2, representada nesta fase por algo como:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:189: Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:274: - contract boundary B2 <-> Paperclip/Perseus\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:329: ## G. Integra��o Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:331: ### Pe�a do lado Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:335: - activar e monitorar o B2 do lado Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:339: ### Pe�as a alinhar do lado Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:448: ## Fase 7 - Definir a pe�a do Paperclip (`Perseus`) e a boundary do B2\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:451: Fechar a integra��o real do lado Paperclip.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:458: - decidir como o primeiro teste S3-only ser� tratado do lado Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:461: O Paperclip consegue disparar o B2 e interpretar correctamente o seu estado externo.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:471: - Paperclip consegue iniciar o B2\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:500: 1. o Paperclip consegue iniciar o B2\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:555: ### Risco 4 - O Paperclip acabar a conhecer demais o interior do B2\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:605: - a decis�o de tratar o B2 como unidade paperclip-facing\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_PLAN.md:652: 4. discutir/definir Perseus e a interface concreta do lado Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_STATE.md:39: - the first Paperclip-side E2E narrow flow succeeded from boundary bootstrap to `b2_completed.json`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_STATE.md:47: - CLI primitive for the current `supervisor -> operator` hop\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_STATE.md:66: - macro checkpoint emission requirement\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_STATE.md:76: ### Paperclip/OpenClaw boundary flow\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_STATE.md:105: exec -> openclaw agent --agent <operator_id> --session-id <unique-run-operator-session> --message \"...\" --json --timeout 1800\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_STATE.md:109: Default CLI session reuse is not acceptable as a production assumption.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_STATE.md:113: The S3 supervisor must treat the operator registry as closed for the current phase:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_STATE.md:145: ### ACP as central orchestration substrate\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\EXECUTION_STATE.md:154: ### Basic Paperclip/OpenClaw viability\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:30: ## 2. False blocker: ACP as if it were the orchestration substrate\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:33: ACP kept appearing as a blocker when trying to prove `supervisor -> operator` launches.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:36: ACP was **not** the right central runtime for this workflow. The actual viable primitive in this environment is:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:43: We stopped treating ACP as the required execution substrate for S3 orchestration and hard-pinned the supervisor-side runtime path to the CLI primitive above.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:46: - Do not default to ACP for workflow orchestration.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:47: - Treat ACP as optional/auxiliary, not foundational, unless a future sector proves otherwise.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:118: It proved that nested launch did not actually require ACP in the way we had been assuming.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:129: Several validation runs ended as `degraded_completed`.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:133: In narrow validation runs, `degraded_completed` can mean two very different things:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:251: - supervisor drifting into ACP fallback\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:257: - \"the whole architecture is impossible without ACP\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:279: ### Before letting Paperclip rely on a sector\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:290: - ACP is the default solution\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\POSTMORTEM_AND_LEARNINGS_2026-04-03.md:328: Future sectors should use that file as the practical gate before asking Paperclip/Perseus to rely on a new sector.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\REAL_RUN_VALIDATION_2026-04-03.md:4: Validate the next execution tranche for Block 2 with a real OpenClaw path narrower than the full sector: bootstrap B2/S3 correctly, run at least one real S3 operator agent, validate its output structurally, compile sector artifacts, and observe what still blocks Paperclip/Perseus activation of `b2_director -> S3`.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\REAL_RUN_VALIDATION_2026-04-03.md:33: - **does not claim block success when the compiled sector status is only `degraded_completed`**\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\REAL_RUN_VALIDATION_2026-04-03.md:86:    The compile status for the narrow run is `degraded_completed`, not `completed`.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\REAL_RUN_VALIDATION_2026-04-03.md:91: 5. **Paperclip -> Perseus -> b2_director activation is not yet proven operationally.**\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\REAL_RUN_VALIDATION_2026-04-03.md:92:    No live Paperclip-facing trigger was exercised here.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\REAL_RUN_VALIDATION_2026-04-03.md:95: Paperclip should **not** yet assume that creating Perseus is enough to activate a coherent `b2_director -> S3` runtime.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\REAL_RUN_VALIDATION_2026-04-03.md:119:   - `status = degraded_completed`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\REAL_RUN_VALIDATION_2026-04-03.md:120:   - reason: `ACP runtime backend unavailable; real op_s3_human_subject_extractor session could not be launched.`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\REAL_RUN_VALIDATION_2026-04-03.md:130: - CLI error: `Unknown agent id \"b2_director\"`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\REAL_RUN_VALIDATION_2026-04-03.md:139: 2. Understand why nested real agent launches from `sm_s3_visual_planning` report `ACP runtime backend unavailable`, despite direct top-level operator invocations working from the shell.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\REAL_RUN_VALIDAT