: No caso do S3, o workflow paperclip-facing do sector deve:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:95: 1. receber o payload do Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:101: 7. devolver ao Paperclip o estado final desse trecho\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:107: O Paperclip **n�o invoca os operadores do S3**.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:109: O Paperclip tamb�m **n�o deve, idealmente, invocar directamente a topologia interna do sector**.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:114: Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:115:   -> workflow / mini-orquestrador paperclip-facing do S3\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:126: ### Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:132: ### Workflow paperclip-facing do S3\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:134: - tradu��o do job do Paperclip para o contexto do sector\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:137: - normaliza��o de output do sector para o ecossistema Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:158: O workflow paperclip-facing do S3 **n�o � o c�rebro do sector**.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:173: Ainda sem nome definitivo, o sector poder� ter um entrypoint paperclip-facing como:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:183: - receber o job do Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:208: - cada workflow representa uma unidade paperclip-facing\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:210: - Paperclip encadeia workflows\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:221: - o supervisor do S3 n�o precisa ser a primeira interface exposta ao Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:230: **Paperclip invoca workflows.**  \r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:242: 1. **workflow paperclip-facing (`w3_visual_planning.py`)**\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:256: - boundary layer entre Paperclip e OpenClaw\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:262: 1. receber o payload do Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:269: ### Payload m�nimo recebido do Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\architecture.md:550: - a separa��o Paperclip -> workflow -> supervisor -> operators\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\post_dispatch.md:492: O supervisor n�o precisa necessariamente de chamar o S4 directamente, caso essa responsabilidade fique com Paperclip/workflow.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\runtime_layout.md:276: ## Operator registry\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\supervisor.md:5: Este documento descreve o papel do supervisor do S3 e o que acontece **depois que ele � activado** pelo workflow paperclip-facing do sector.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\supervisor.md:23: Ele n�o � a boundary layer com o Paperclip. Essa responsabilidade pertence ao workflow paperclip-facing do sector.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\supervisor.md:232: exec -> openclaw agent --agent <operator_agent_id> --session-id <unique-run-operator-session> --message \"...\" --json --timeout 1800\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\supervisor.md:235: Ou seja, nesta fase o supervisor deve usar um launch real via CLI/OpenClaw agent e n�o ACP/sessions_spawn para este hop.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\supervisor.md:239: - n�o tentar ACP como caminho prim�rio\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\supervisor.md:247: - espelhar o resultado final do sector no macro checkpoint do bloco (`b2/checkpoints/s3_completed.json` ou `s3_failed.json`)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\supervisor_runtime_contract.md:61: No ambiente actual, a primitive oficial do primeiro run narrow deixa de ser ACP/sessions_spawn.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\supervisor_runtime_contract.md:72: - ACP est� indispon�vel como backend operativo para este hop\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\supervisor_runtime_contract.md:86: - **n�o** tentar ACP primeiro\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\workflow_bootstrap.md:5: Este documento detalha o que o workflow paperclip-facing do S3 dever� fazer **antes** de activar o supervisor `sm_s3_visual_planning`.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\workflow_bootstrap.md:24: - boundary layer entre Paperclip e OpenClaw\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\workflow_bootstrap.md:46: 1. receber o payload do Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\S3\\workflow_bootstrap.md:56: ## Payload m�nimo esperado do Paperclip\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\